      {
        "clause": "10.2.1",
        "feature": "Function calls, this binding, and lazy arguments object materialization",
        "status": "Supported with Limitations",
        "specUrl": "https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-ecmascript-function-objects-call-thisargument-argumentslist",
        "testScripts": [
          "tests/Jroc.Tests/Function/JavaScript/Function_Arguments_Basics.js",
          "tests/Jroc.Tests/Function/JavaScript/Function_Arguments_MappedParameterAliasing.js",
          "tests/Jroc.Tests/Function/JavaScript/Function_Arguments_Unmapped_StrictAndComplex.js",
          "tests/Jroc.Tests/Function/JavaScript/Function_Call_Basic.js",
          "tests/Jroc.Tests/Function/JavaScript/Function_ObjectLiteralMethod_ThisBinding.js",
          "tests/Jroc.Tests/Classes/JavaScript/Classes_ClassMethod_ReturnsThis_IsSelf_Log.js"
        ],
        "notes": "Delegate-backed user functions support ordinary calls, receiver-sensitive method calls, lexical this for arrow functions, and lazy materialization of a dedicated arguments object when the implicit binding is referenced. Non-arrow functions use mapped arguments objects for non-strict simple parameter lists and unmapped arguments objects for strict-mode or complex parameter lists; remaining gaps are the narrower 10.4.4 descriptor/invariant edge cases rather than wholesale lack of arguments-object support."
      },
      {
        "clause": "10.2.2",
        "feature": "Constructor calls and new.target-aware function execution",
        "status": "Supported with Limitations",
        "specUrl": "https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-ecmascript-function-objects-construct-argumentslist-newtarget",
        "testScripts": [
          "tests/Jroc.Tests/Function/JavaScript/Function_NewTarget_NewVsCall.js",
          "tests/Jroc.Tests/Function/JavaScript/Function_NewTarget_Arrow_Inherits.js",
          "tests/Jroc.Tests/Classes/JavaScript/Classes_Constructor_ReturnObjectOverridesThis.js",
          "tests/Jroc.Tests/Classes/JavaScript/Classes_DeclareEmptyClass.js"
        ],
        "notes": "JROC constructs delegate-backed functions and class constructors by creating an instance, binding this, and forwarding a newTarget value into the call path. Constructor return override works, but super/inheritance semantics and full OrdinaryCreateFromConstructor behavior remain incomplete."
      },
      {
        "clause": "10.2.4",
        "feature": "Restricted function caller/arguments properties",
        "status": "Supported with Limitations",
        "specUrl": "https://tc39.es/ecma262/#sec-addrestrictedfunctionproperties",
